          "$type": "text",
          "text": "{\"week_number\":1,\"phase_type\":\"Base\",\"weekly_target_km\":42,\"is_deload_week\":false,\"days\":[{\"day_of_week\":0,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"LongRun\",\"notes\":\"Easy long run at 6:27/km. Keep effort conversational throughout. Target 14–15 km. This is your aerobic foundation — no heroics today.\"},{\"day_of_week\":1,\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Full rest or gentle walking. Your body adapts during recovery, not during the run itself.\"},{\"day_of_week\":2,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"notes\":\"Easy run at 5:50–6:27/km, 8 km. Focus on relaxed form and breathing. This builds aerobic base without accumulating fatigue.\"},{\"day_of_week\":3,\"slot_type\":\"CrossTrain\",\"workout_type\":\"CrossTrain\",\"notes\":\"Low-impact cross-training: cycling, swimming, or yoga. 30–45 min. Keeps aerobic stimulus while protecting your legs — especially smart given your IT band history.\"},{\"day_of_week\":4,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Tempo\",\"notes\":\"Threshold workout: 2 km warm-up at easy pace, 4 km at 4:50/km, 2 km cool-down. Total 8 km. Threshold work builds your lactate clearance — the engine behind your 1:45 goal.\"},{\"day_of_week\":5,\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Rest day. You've earned it. Let the tempo work absorb before your weekend runs.\"},{\"day_of_week\":6,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"notes\":\"Easy run at 5:50–6:27/km, 7 km. Shake out the legs ahead of Sunday's long run. Keep it genuinely easy — this is a support run, not a workout.\"}],\"week_summary\":\"Welcome to Week 1, Lee. This is a Base phase week designed to re-establish your aerobic foundation and bring your weekly volume up gently from your recent inconsistency. Your VDOT of 42 and your 10K time tell us you have real fitness to build on — the goal this week is to consolidate that, not push beyond it. The tempo run on Thursday is your one quality session; everything else serves recovery and aerobic development. With your IT band history, the cross-training day on Wednesday is a deliberate choice to keep load on your legs manageable as we ramp up. Target 42 km total this week.\"}"
        }
      ]
    }
